                "created_at": "2019-01-08T17:14:50.875Z",
                "cooked": "<p>Hey HPC nerds! I\u2019m putting together a little tutorial and introduction to job arrays (very simple) and the most important detail is having a list of compelling reasons we would want to use them in the first place, say, over something standard like submission with sbatch. Let\u2019s put our heads together and think! I\u2019m relatively new to using them so my list is likely limited.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Running a randomized simulation many times, with output files numbered from some 1\u2026N. The output files can be numbered according to the array index. This means we use the array index as a variable to name our output files.</li>\n<li>Running an analysis over inputs, where each input is named according to the array index, and outputs follow suit. This could also be applied to directory names.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>What do others think?</p>",
                "post_number": 1,
                "post_type": 1,
                "updated_at": "2019-06-20T15:14:47.283Z",
